Class ObjectEnum<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.comphenix.protocol.reflect.ObjectEnum<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PacketType.Handshake.Client, PacketType.Handshake.Server, PacketType.Legacy.Client, PacketType.Legacy.Server, PacketType.Login.Client, PacketType.Login.Server, PacketType.Play.Client, PacketType.Play.Server, PacketType.Status.Client, PacketType.Status.Server

    public class ObjectEnum<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Represents a more modern object-based enum.

    This is useful if you want the flexibility of a modern Java enum, but don't want to prevent the creation of additional members dynamically.

    Author:
    Kristian
